  "body": "# Problem\r\nWhen FaceID fails, the user is directed to the password unlock screen with no opportunity to try again.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nRespond to callback of FaceID failure\r\n\r\n- The Face ID check should not happen on a blank background like it is right now, it should happen on top of the pin pad;\r\n- A failed Face ID should allow to enter the passcode instead or re-trigger the Face ID  check\r\nhere's where it's a password, not passcode\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1399\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2020-01-22 at 17 43 19\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3115606/72903697-c2947f80-3d3e-11ea-8e64-ccc682988c80.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n## Acceptance Criteria\r\nFaceID behavior is implemented according to design in [Figma](https://www.figma.com/file/dEIljL7UPbXgsZUA0Q4qlE5E/Onboarding?node-id=5038%3A214)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nInvestigate if the behavior can/should be the same for fingerprint\r\n\r\n## Future Steps\r\n\r\n- Create multiaccount\r\n- Enable FaceID\r\n- Close app (don't sign out, settings will be reset until this issue is resolved: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/9763#issuecomment-573052216\r\n- Open with FaceID, hold phone away from face - make FaceID fail\r\n- Tap Try FaceID again\r\n\r\n",
